@Dextromancer
Greetings Archons, When I was made one of the original Archons, I was told that we are community representatives and that we would play a large part in how Dextroverse would be shaped. However, I feel that since we trust you guys to make good choices about how you want Dextroverse to be, we should show that. Effective immediately, you will be granted the following permissions: 1. The ability to text mute users via the @deleted-role role. 2. The ability to promote users only to Robot and Dextromancer as you see fit. Promotions to other ranks will be done as they were before. You may not promote people to custom ranks, Autonomous, Self-Aware, Sentinel, or Observer. You may not create new roles without asking an Officer first. 3. You can mute, deafen, move, and disconnect users in the Voice Chat space. 4. You will be able to delete offending text from text channels as well as change the nicknames of users who have offending material in it. You may not change nicknames of people unless their nick is an offensive one. 5. You will receive a new channel called #archon-observer-log where you will document moderating duties. If you delete text, screenshot it, and post an incident report. If you change someone's offending name, you must document it. Everything must be documented. You will also gain access to the Audit Log. 6. We are trusting you to not abuse the new powers you are given. Trust is essential for this to work out. Trust is key. 7. All Archons will receive DJ and Groovy DJ roles so they may assist in curating music on the bots. The only rule that is enforced in terms of that is that you may not skip people's music unless they say you can. We hope that you'll find awesome ways of contributing to the community with your new found legs. You are an important part of the community and it's time that you get to feel like you are. We love you and are so happy you're part of our team. -- @Chemical on behalf of the mod team
